1 AN ACT relating to cigar bars.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 65 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Cigar bar" means an establishment that:
7 1. Holds a valid license or permit for the on-premises consumption of
8 alcoholic beverages;
9 2. Generates a portion of its gross income from the on-site sale of cigars
10 and the rental of humidors;
11 3. Does not knowingly sell products or services, or permit entrance to the
12 premises, to persons under twenty-one (21) years of age; and
13 4. Does not permit the use of electronic cigarettes or vapor products or
14 the smoking of products other than cigars inside the premises; and
15 (b) "Local government" means a city, county, urban-county government,
16 consolidated local government, charter county government, unified local
17 government, or special district.
18 (2) An ordinance, rule, or policy adopted by a local government that prohibits or
19 otherwise restricts smoking shall not prohibit or restrict the smoking of cigars
20 within the interior space of a cigar bar. Any ordinance, rule, or policy to the
21 contrary shall be unenforceable as it relates to a cigar bar.
22 (3) (a) A cigar bar that shares a physical wall or common, enclosed air space with
23 any other structure shall be constructed in a manner or implement
24 measures to ensure that smoke from the cigar bar does not pass into the
25 interior or enclosed air spaces of those other structures.
26 (b) The owner of a cigar bar shall provide a smoke-free space for the delivery of
27 supplies, mail, and other items to the premises by persons other than
